{"id":1377969704,"question_id":9,"lang":"c","lang_name":"C","time":"4 months, 4 weeks","timestamp":1725384568,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"4 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1377969704/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Palindrome Number","memory":"7.8 MB","code":"#include <stdbool.h>\n\nbool isPalindrome(int x) {\n    // If x is negative or ends with 0 but is not 0 itself, it is not a palindrome\n    if (x < 0 || (x % 10 == 0 && x != 0)) {\n        return false;\n    }\n\n    int reversedNumber = 0;\n    \n    // Reverse half of the number\n    while (x > reversedNumber) {\n        reversedNumber = reversedNumber * 10 + x % 10;\n        x /= 10;\n    }\n\n    // The number is a palindrome if the first half equals the reversed second half\n    // or the first half equals the reversed second half after removing the middle digit (for odd-length numbers)\n    return x == reversedNumber || x == reversedNumber / 10;\n}\n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"palindrome-number","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
